      <abstract>
        <p>In this paper we propose the synthesis of 2-(2-(6-chloro-9H-purin-9-yl)ethoxy)-6-isobutoxy-tetrahydro-2H-pyran-3-ol as a new potential antiviral agent Its structure has been confirmed by IR, <sup>1</sup>H-NMR, <sup>13</sup>C-NMR, UV and Mass spectroscopic data.</p>
      </abstract>
